"***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Mers will escape from Chifrex?\"***\n5. Moderately likely\nMers has already demonstrated a willingness to fight back and has attempted an escape, showing resourcefulness and agility. However, he is currently disarmed and being closely watched by Chifrex and his gunmen. The fact that he was able to retain and protect his fountain pen, which might be a tool for his escape or communication, suggests he might still have a plan up his sleeve.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\n6. Very suspenseful\nThe passage is full of action and tension. Mers's attempt to rescue Vesper and his subsequent defeat by Chifrex's quick action, along with the mention of Chifrex seemingly anticipating Mers's intentions, creates a high level of suspense. The unknown fate of the fountain pen, a seemingly ordinary object now imbued with importance, adds to the intrigue."